# DropVentures stores keys in browser localStorage via the Settings modal,
# so an .env is NOT required.
#
# If you want to pre-populate keys for local dev (e.g. when developing the
# template itself), you can wire these up to be read by your own code.
# Out-of-the-box the template ignores them and asks the user via the UI.

# RUNFLOW_API_KEY=rf_...
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
